](url)

State Website Screenshots - https://covidtracking.com/api/v1/screenshots.json (link from https://covidtracking.com/api) yields:

`{"code":404,"error":"404 - NOT FOUND","pathname":"/v1/screenshots.json"}
`

While working on [tests for cumulative (+/-) values](https://github.com/COVID19Tracking/website/pull/510), I encountered 4 anomalies in [States Historical Data](https://covidtracking.com/api). There are some cumulative entries that are *less than* the value for previous date. This should never happen if values are cumulative.

I know the state websites are the "source of truth" but anomalies like this suggest that their public websites may have experienced a sort of regression and I wonder if we shouldn't correct it or seek clarification? Anyways, I thought I would open the issue to at least document these somewhere:


**RI**

